-- Lan Airlines Quarterly Profit Jumps to $60.6 Million, Beating Estimates
-- Eduardo Thomson
-- 2010-07-27T20:19:12Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-07-27/lan-airlines-quarterly-profit-jumps-to-60-6-million-beating-estimates.html

          
          
             Lan Airlines SA, Latin America’s
largest airline by market value, reported second-quarter profit
of $60.6 million.  
 Net income for the three months through June rose from
$4.23 million a year earlier, according to a statement posted
today on the website of Chile’s securities regulator.  
 The average estimate of three analysts surveyed by
Bloomberg News was for quarterly profit of $58.8 million.  
